{
  "body": "\r\ndoc/Language/5to6-nutshell.pod6 has sections like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n=begin code :preamble<no strict;> :ok-test<dd>\r\n# Perl 6\r\n    dd $foo, $bar, @baz;\r\n# Output\r\n    Int $foo = 42\r\n    Int $bar = 44\r\n    Array @baz = [16, 32, 64, \"Hike!\"]\r\n=end code\r\n```\r\nThis puts all the code and output together as a single perl6 code block (which may or may not compile)\r\n\r\nOther doc sections either have a separately formatted output block (which is then exempt from testing), or show the output in a comment in the code block, e.g.:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsay @flat.elems;            # OUTPUT: «6␤»\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe should have a uniform style for showing code output (maybe even having a CSS style and showing it as a separate block in the rendered HTML)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
